1.what is GraphQL
- GraphQL is a new API standard that provides a more efficient, powerful and flexible alternative to REST
- Created by Facebook
- Connect with multiple datasources, Mysql, MongoDB, Postgres
- Declarative data fetching
- Expose only single endpoint
2. GraphQL addvantages
Avoid multiple calls
3. GraphQL vs REST
+ GraphQL
- one route
- Not based on HTTP verbs
- Autogenerated docs
- Data Typing
+ REST
- Multiple routes
- Base on HTPP verbs
- Versioning
